│   9 // This pass transforms loops by placing phi nodes at the end of the      │
│ loops for                                                                     │
│  10 // all values that are live across the loop boundary.  For example, it    │
│ turns                                                                         │
│  11 // the left into the right code:                                          │
│  12 //                                                                        │
│  13 // for (...)                for (...)                                     │
│  14 //   if (c)                   if (c)                                      │
│  15 //     X1 = ...                 X1 = ...                                  │
│  16 //   else                     else                                        │
│  17 //     X2 = ...                 X2 = ...                                  │
│  18 //   X3 = phi(X1, X2)         X3 = phi(X1, X2)                            │
│  19 // ... = X3 + 4             X4 = phi(X3)                                  │
│  20 //                          ... = X4 + 4                                  │
│  21 //                                                                        │
│  22 // This is still valid LLVM; the extra phi nodes are purely redundant,    │
│ and will                                                                      │
│  23 // be trivially eliminated by InstCombine.  The major benefit of this     │
│  24 // transformation is that it makes many other loop optimizations, such as │
│  25 // LoopUnswitching, simpler.                                              │
│  26 //                                                                        │
